<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/60077902-moses-shuldiner"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1475087615i/60077902._UY100_CR12,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/60077902-moses-shuldiner">Moses Shuldiner</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This book is a brilliant parody of conspiracy theories. It does this by having the protagonist so quickly enmeshed in a conspiracy theory that she exp<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This book is a brilliant parody of conspiracy theories. It does this by having the protagonist so quickly enmeshed in a conspiracy theory that she explains history and almost every event in her daily life as part of this conspiracy . At the same time she wonders if she has a mental health issue or is in the throes of addiction. The meaning of the title is only revealed and illuminated as the last phrase in the novel.<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
