<span id="freeTextContainer9840488734077744180">Maybe 3.5 stars<br/><br/>It was weird! It was unique!<br/><br/>Hey, Thomas Pynchon - could you write us a book where a woman goes to oversee the estate of a real estate mogul and along the way deals with her DJ husband on LSD, an adulterous pedophilic lover, a Nazi psychiatrist on a shooting spree - all in search of information about a secret society who&apos;s only anti-government movement is to run their own postal system (which she becomes intrigued about because of a play she sees with one word that seems out of pla</span>
  <span id="freeText9840488734077744180" style="display:none">Maybe 3.5 stars<br /><br />It was weird! It was unique!<br /><br />Hey, Thomas Pynchon - could you write us a book where a woman goes to oversee the estate of a real estate mogul and along the way deals with her DJ husband on LSD, an adulterous pedophilic lover, a Nazi psychiatrist on a shooting spree - all in search of information about a secret society who's only anti-government movement is to run their own postal system (which she becomes intrigued about because of a play she sees with one word that seems out of place).<br /><br />Thomas Pynchon: Sure - no problem! As long as I can make it jump haphazardly to a different part of the story every few paragraphs and leave everyone hanging in the end . . .</span>
